==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dumdum bullet
<hw>Dum"dum bul"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A kind of
man-stopping bullet, designed to fragment inside the body and thus
inflict a severed and painful wound; -- so named from
<etsep>Dumdum</etsep>, in India, where bullets are manufactured for the
Indian army.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dumetose</ent>⟦br⟧
